Domestic transactions
	695 - Transactions without the flow of funds
		B - Drawdown and repayments of short-term foreign currency loans made by domestic banks
		C - Provisions or return of foreign exchange margins
		D - Realized foreign exchange transaction losses or gains
		E - Interest income or expenses on foreign currency loans
		F - Drawdown and repayments of medium and long-term foreign currency loans made by domestic banks
		G - Unrealized gains/losses measured at a fair value
		R - Receipts and payments for goods between domestic customers
		S - Domestic receipts and payments involving foreign currency denominated investment
		T - Domestic transfer receipts and payments between customers
		L - Domestic receipts and payments between customers involving foreign currency loans
		P - Domestic service receipts and payments between customers
		Q - Domestic Carbon emission rights trading receipts and payments
		N - Receipts and payments of domestic transactions related money other than those described above (e.g. bank fees, tax withholding by banks, cash collaterals for local securities lending, foreign currency time deposit loans, etc.)
		Same customer’s foreign currency purchased only for deposit without remitting into another local or foreign account; selling foreign currency that was originally purchased only for deposit
